1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:12,000
A generalist robot needs task intent that survives a new scene, layout, or body.

2
00:00:12,000 --> 00:00:25,000
Direct replay stores a path. LfO abstracts the purpose behind the path.

3
00:00:25,000 --> 00:00:39,000
Language and vision are compressed into a compact task model.

4
00:00:39,000 --> 00:00:51,000
What-to-do names the primitive operation required by the task.

5
00:00:51,000 --> 00:01:03,000
Where-to-do grounds that operation in objects, handles, axes, or target regions.

6
00:01:03,000 --> 00:01:18,000
The skill-agent library supplies how-to-do through feedback-driven robot action.

7
00:01:18,000 --> 00:01:31,000
The same task model can produce different feasible motions on different robot bodies.

8
00:01:31,000 --> 00:01:38,000
Chapter two asks how the primitive skill vocabulary should be defined.

